The World Monuments Watch is a flagship advocacy program of the [[New York City|New York]]-based private [[non-profit organization]] [[World Monuments Fund]] (WMF) that calls international attention to [[cultural heritage]] around the world that is threatened by [[neglect]], [[vandalism]], [[war|conflict]], or [[natural disaster|disaster]].<ref name=press_release>{{cite web | title = The 2016 World Monuments Watch Includes 50 At-Risk Cultural Heritage Sites in 36 Countries | author = Daniela Stigh | date = 15 October 2015 | publisher = World Monuments Fund | url = https://www.wmf.org/press-release/2016-world-monuments-watch-includes-50-risk-cultural-heritage-sites-36-countries|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref>
