omaia]], similar to [[placental]] mammals.<!--125 Ma--> |- | align=center| 110 Ma – 90 Ma ||[[Late Cretaceous]]: [[Cenomanian]], [[Turonian]], [[Coniacian]], [[Santonian]] || [[Supervolcano]] in eastern Australia sends particles to west coast.<!--106 Ma--><ref>{{cite journal|author=M. Barham ''et al.''|date=Jul 2016|title=The answers are blowin' in the wind: Ultra-distal ashfall zircons, indicators of Cretaceous super-eruptions in eastern Gondwana|journal=Geology|doi=10.1130/G38000.1|url=http://geology.gsapubs.org/content/44/8/643|volume=44|issue=8|pages=643–646|bibcode=2016Geo....44..643B}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Giant ancient supervolcanoes threw rock right across Australia I|journal=New Scientist|date=Aug 27, 2016|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg23130881-800-giant-ancient-supervolcanoes-threw-rock-right-across-australia/}}</ref> [[Bee]]s. [[Mammal]]s diversify into many forms.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Mammals not such late developers, after all|journal=New Scientist|date=Mar 28, 2007|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg19325975.100-mammals-not-such-late-developers-after-all}}</ref> [[Cenomanian-Turonian boundary event]] (oceans anoxic for half a million years),<!-- 93 Ma ago--><ref>{{cite journal|title=Submarine eruption bled Earth’s oceans of oxygen|journal=New Scientist|date=Jul 16, 2008|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg19926655.300-submarine-eruption-bled-earths-oceans-of-oxygen}}</ref> extinction of [[ichthyosaur]]s. |- | align=center| 90 Ma – 70 Ma ||[[Campanian]] & [[Maastrichtian]] stages of the Cretaceous || Dominance of [[angiosperm]] [[rosid]]s. [[Rocky Mountains]] begin forming.<!--80 Ma--> [[Zealandia]] breaks away from [[Australia]].<!--60 to 85 Ma--> [[Mosasaur]]s are dominant marine predator.<!--Last 20 Ma of Cretaceous--> |- | align=center| 70 Ma – 55 Ma ||[[Paleocene]] (66–56 Ma)|| Evidence for [[grass]]es in dinosaur dung ([[coprolites]]). [[Crocodile]]s.<!--Crocodyloids from 72-66 Ma--> [[Madagascar]] breaks 