===18 million years ago to 5.5 million years ago=== {| class="wikitable" |- ! style="background:silver;" abbr="Interval"|'''Time interval, before the present time. a=[[annus]] (year)''' ! style="background:silver;" abbr="Period"|'''[[List of time periods|Period]]''' ! style="background:silver;" abbr="Event"| '''Event, [[invention]] or historical development''' |- | align=center| 18 Ma – 14 Ma ||[[Miocene]], [[Burdigalian age]], [[Langhian age]] || [[Antarctica]] becomes mostly ice-covered.<!--14 or 15 Ma ago--> Africa/Arabia collides with Eurasia, end of [[Tethys Sea]]. [[Columbia River basalts]].<!--Mostly 17 to 14 Ma--> First [[Deinotherium|deinotheres]], similar to an elephant but with tusks on lower jaw.<!--Middle Miocene--> [[Nördlinger Ries]] impact crater.<!--14.4 Ma--> [[Mid-Miocene Climatic Optimum]], [[Middle Miocene disruption]]. [[Hominidae]] split from [[gibbon]]s.<!--15 (or 18) Ma ago--> |- | align=center| 14 Ma – 11 Ma ||[[Miocene]], [[Serravallian age]] || Last of the [[Adapiformes|adapiforms]]. [[Anoiapithecus]], one of the first [[hominid]]s, in Spain.<!--11.9 Ma ago--> |- | align=center| 11 Ma – 9 Ma ||[[Miocene]], [[Tortonian age]] || [[Olympic Mountains]] reach present height |- | align=center| 9 Ma – 7 Ma ||[[Miocene]], [[Tortonian age]]|| First [[Gigantopithecus]], an [[ape]] almost {{convert|10|ft|m}} tall.<!--From 9 Ma--> [[C4 carbon fixation|C4 grasses]] become common. [[Crocodile]]s cross the Atlantic to America.<!--7 Ma ago--><ref>[https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn20464-crocodiles-swam-the-atlantic-to-reach-america.html "Crocodiles swam the Atlantic to reach America"], by Michael Marshall, ''New Scientist'', May 14, 2011, p. 16.</ref> |- | align=center| 7 Ma – 5.5 Ma ||[[Miocene]], [[Messinian age]] || [[Graecopithecus]] ("Greek ape"), possibly ancestor of [[hominin]]s.<!--ca. 7.2 Ma--> "[[Toumaï]]", of species [[Sahelanthropus tchadensis]], shows some human traits.<!--6.2 to 6.4 Ma ago--> First [[Thylacosmilus]], sabre-toothed marsupial of South America. [[Orrorin tugenensis]], possible hominin.<!--5.8 Ma--> Apparent hominin [[footprint]]s near Trachilos, on [[Crete]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Gerard D. Gierliński et al.|title=Possible hominin footprints from the late Miocene (c. 5.7 Ma) of Crete?|journal=Proceedings of the Geologists' Association|date=Oct 2017|doi=10.1016/j.pgeola.2017.07.006|volume=128|issue=5–6|pages=697–710}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Colin Barras|title=Footprints hint that humans are from Europe|journal=New Scientist|date=Sep 9, 2017|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg23531424-600-controversial-footprints-suggest-we-evolved-in-europe-not-africa}}</ref><!--5.7 Ma--> [[Mediterranean Sea]] dries up ([[Messinian Event]]).<!--5.96 to 5.33 Ma--> |}
