early-humans-were-butchers-34-million-years-ago.html}}</ref> Human line loses fur (possibly).<!--3.3 Ma ago--><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Elaine Morgan|authorlink1=Elaine Morgan (writer)|title=Why are we the naked ape?|journal=New Scientist|date=16 Sep 2009|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20327261.000-why-are-we-the-naked-ape}}</ref> Possible time of [[Isthmus of Panama]] connecting South and [[Central America]]. [[Great American Interchange]].<!--3 Ma--> [[Lucy (Australopithecus)|Lucy]], member of the species ''[[Australopithecus afarensis]]''.<!--3.2 Ma--> First [[Megatherium americanum]], a [[giant sloth]].<!--2.8 Ma?--> |- | align=center| 2.8 Ma – 2.2 Ma || Beginning of [[Pleistocene]], [[Gelasian]], [[Lower Paleolithic]] || Beginning of the current [[ice age]], known as the [[Quaternary glaciation]]. ''[[Homo habilis]]'' appears.<!--2.8 Ma--> [[Pliocene-Pleistocene boundary extinction]] of marine [[megafauna]], including the [[Megalodon]] shark,<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Catalina Pimiento et al.|title=The Pliocene marine megafauna extinction and its impact on functional diversity|journal=[[Nature Ecology & Evolution]]|date=Jun 2017|doi=10.1038/s41559-017-0223-6|volume=1|issue=8|pages=1100–1106}}</ref> possibly caused by a nearby supernova or [[Pliocene#Supernovae|supernovas]] of the [[Scorpius-Centaurus Association]], which deposited [[Iron 60|<sup>60</sup>Fe]] on Earth.<!--2.6 to 2.8 Ma--><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Narciso Benítez et al.|title=Evidence for Nearby Supernova Explosions|journal=[[Physical Review Letters]]|date=Feb 2002|doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.88.081101|bibcode=2002PhRvL..88h1101B|volume=88|issue=8|arxiv=astro-ph/0201018|url=http://cds.cern.ch/record/534437/files/0201018.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Peter Ludwig et al.|title=Time-resolved 2-million-year-old supernova activity discovered in Earth's microfossil record|journal=[[PNAS]]|date=Aug 2016|doi=10.1073/pnas.1601040113|volume=113|issue=33|pages=9232–9237|pmc=4995991|arxiv=1710.09573|bibcode=2016PNAS..113.9232L}}</ref> [[Oldowan]] [[tool]]s used near [[Gona]], [[Ethiopia]].<!--2.6 Ma--> Possible tool use in [[Sivalik Hills]], India.<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Anne Dambricourt Malassé|author2=''et al.''|title=Anthropic activities in the fossiliferous Quranwala Zone, 2.6Ma, Siwaliks of Northwest India, historical context of the discovery and scientific investigations|journal=Comptes Rendus Palevol|date=2016|url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S1631068315001165|doi=10.1016/j.crpv.2015.06.004|volume=15|issue=3–4|pages=295–316}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Asian stone tools hint humans left Africa earlier than thought|journal=New Scientist|date=Feb 6, 2016|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/2076113}}</ref> Impact of [[Eltanin asteroid]] (1 to 4&nbsp;km in diameter) in Pacific.<!--2.5 Ma--> Stone artefacts at [[Longgupo]] (Dragon Bone Slope) in China.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Han|first1=Fei|last2=''et al.''|title=The earliest evidence of hominid settlement in China: Combined electron spin resonance and uranium series (ESR/U-series) dating of mammalian fossil teeth from Longgupo cave|journal=Quaternary International|volume=434|pages=75–83|date=Mar 2015|doi=10.1016/j.quaint.2015.02.025|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/273889449_The_earliest_evidence_of_hominid_settlement_in_China_Combined_electron_spin_resonance_and_uranium_series_ESRU-series_dating_of_mammalian_fossil_teeth_from_Longgupo_cave|bibcode=2017QuInt.434...75H}}</ref> (see also [[Wushan Man]])<!--ca 2.48 Ma--> |- | align=center| 2.2 Ma – 1.8 Ma ||[[Gelasian]] || [[Island Park Caldera]] in Wyoming and Idaho.<!--2.1 Ma--> ''[[Homo erectus]]'' appears.<!--1.9 Ma--> [[Dmanisi Man]] (''Homo erectus georgicus'') in [[Dmanisi]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]<!--1.85 Ma ago--> and in [[Xiaochangliang]], [[China]]. Human-like ''[[Australopithecus sediba]]''.<!--1.95-1.78 Ma--> ''[[Homo ergaster]]'' in Africa.<!--1.9 to 1.4 Ma ago--> First signs of [[Acheulian]]