'''Feudal maintenance''' under [[feudal system]]s of [[government]], was the money payment to [[soldier]]s who fought in the interest and at the command of their [[lord]].  Such soldiers comprised [[Mercenary|private armies]], each with uniquely identifiable [[livery]].  The system of feudal government under which maintenance was paid was most notably present in the late 15th century.

[[Category:Feudalism]]


